# 2026-05-18 05:38:09.043482
+Read docs/ANALYSIS_REPORT.md for the full context, especially the section on Gap 1: Progressive Disclosure UI.
+
+Task: Transform the app's visual design to a premium, Whoop-level look and feel. Focus on the main dashboard (TodayPage) and global CSS.
+
+Requirements:
+1. Progressive disclosure on TodayPage:
+   - Tier 1 (hero): Large Recovery Score ring front and center (~72pt equivalent), with a single readiness status label.
+   - Tier 2 (collapsible): Weekly trend sparklines for HRV, sleep, strain  shown after a tap on the hero ring.
+   - Tier 3 (expandable): Full exercise plan and session details, accessible via a "Подробнее" button.
+2. Typography: Use oversized primary metric typography. Clear hierarchy h1-h4, generous line-height.
+3. Micro-animations: page transitions, card expand/collapse, score ring fill animation on load, smooth tab switches.
+4. High-contrast card system with consistent elevation levels, rounded corners, subtle borders.
+5. Mobile-first: min 48px touch targets, no horizontal scroll, spacing optimized for phones.
+6. All existing functionality must be preserved exactly.
+
+Implement by editing css/styles.css and the TodayPage-related components (ReadinessRing, RecoveryBar, ExerciseCard, TomorrowPreview, TodayPage itself). You may also touch other components for consistency.
+
+Start by reading the current source files, then propose your design changes before writing code.

