+We've just completed architectural refactoring (Task 1). Now implement Task 2: premium visual redesign.
+
+**Goal:** Transform the app's look and feel to match Whoop and Athlytic premium quality.
+
+**Key requirements (implement at your discretion):**
+
+1. **Progressive disclosure on TodayPage:**
+   - Hero: Large Recovery Score ring (SVG, ~72pt equivalent) with readiness status label.
+   - Tapping the ring reveals weekly trend sparklines (HRV, sleep, strain).
+   - Full exercise plan hidden behind "Подробнее" expandable section.
+
+2. **Typography:** Big primary metric numbers, clear hierarchy, comfortable line-height (1.5+).
+
+3. **Micro-animations:** Page transitions, card expand/collapse, score ring fill animation on load, smooth tab switches.
+
+4. **Card system:** High contrast, consistent elevation, rounded corners (16px+), subtle borders. Mobile-first: min 48px touch targets, no horizontal scroll.
+
+5. **Preserve all existing functionality exactly.** No feature may break.
+
+6. **Files to edit:** css/styles.css, TodayPage.js and its sub-components (ReadinessRing.js, RecoveryBar.js, ExerciseCard.js, TomorrowPreview.js). You may also touch other components for consistency.
+
+Start by reading current source files, then propose your design changes before writing code.

